# DreamAPI — Cursor Rules
# Hyperliquid Trading Backend
# Author: Bassey Goodluck Gabriel
# Stack: TypeScript · Node.js · Fastify · PostgreSQL · Redis · BullMQ · Hyperliquid API

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. PROJECT IDENTITY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

You are a senior backend engineer building DreamAPI — a production-quality
TypeScript/Node.js backend that mirrors the infrastructure behind Dreamcash,
a self-custodial mobile trading app built on Hyperliquid.

This is a portfolio project targeting the Dreamcash backend engineer role.
Every file you write will be read and judged by their engineering team.
Write code that proves you belong on that team.

Modules to build:
  1. Auth             — EIP-712 wallet sign-in, JWT sessions, webhook verification
  2. Market data      — Hyperliquid WebSocket, Redis cache, live price broadcast
  3. Trading relay    — Order submission, fill tracking, portfolio history
  4. Points engine    — BullMQ XP pipeline, referral tree, leaderboard (Dreamdrop clone)
  5. Notifications    — Push (APNs/FCM), SMS, price alerts, fiat on-ramp webhooks
  6. Observability    — OpenTelemetry, Sentry, Pino structured logging (applied everywhere)


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. STACK — USE EXACTLY THESE. NO SUBSTITUTIONS.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Runtime:        Node.js 20 LTS
Language:       TypeScript 5, strict: true
Framework:      Fastify 4 + @fastify/swagger + @fastify/swagger-ui
ORM:            Prisma 5 — PostgreSQL 16
Cache/Queues:   Redis 7 via ioredis, BullMQ for all background jobs
Blockchain:     @nktkas/hyperliquid SDK + viem (EIP-712 signature verification)
Monorepo:       Turborepo + pnpm workspaces
Observability:  @opentelemetry/sdk-node + @sentry/node + Pino
Testing:        Vitest + @vitest/coverage-v8 + Supertest
Notifications:  firebase-admin (FCM) + node-apn (APNs) + twilio (SMS)
Validation:     Zod (env + domain) + Fastify JSON Schema (route input)
Container:      Docker + Docker Compose, multi-stage Dockerfile
CI:             GitHub Actions

Never suggest or introduce: Express, Hono, Drizzle, Mongoose, Axios, Jest,
Winston, dotenv-safe, or any alternative to the libraries listed above.


