            leaderboardSnapshot)
          - Job payload interfaces
          - Confirm: TypeScript compiles, queues connect to Redis

Step 6:   apps/api bootstrap
          - buildApp() factory, Pino, Sentry, OTel, Swagger, CORS, rate-limit
          - GET /health endpoint
          - Confirm: server starts, /health returns 200, /docs renders

Step 7:   GitHub Actions CI
          - ci.yml with lint + typecheck + test + docker-build jobs
          - Confirm: pipeline passes on a clean push

Step 8:   Auth module
          - POST /auth/nonce, /auth/verify, /auth/refresh, /auth/logout
          - verifyWebhook middleware
          - requireAuth preHandler
          - Integration tests for all auth routes
          - Confirm: full sign-in flow works end-to-end

Step 9:   Market data module
          - HyperliquidWsClient started in app.ts
          - Redis cache writes on allMids + l2Book events
          - GET /markets, GET /markets/:symbol/orderbook, GET /markets/:symbol/price
          - WebSocket broadcast server
          - Confirm: connect to WS, subscribe to BTC, receive live prices

Step 10:  apps/worker bootstrap
          - Worker entry point, Pino, Sentry, OTel
          - BullMQ worker setup (empty processors registered)
          - Confirm: worker starts, connects to Redis, shows queue names

Step 11:  Trading module
          - POST /orders with risk validation
          - GET /orders, GET /positions, GET /portfolio/history
          - Fill tracking via Hyperliquid userEvents subscription
          - xpEvents job published on fill
          - Integration tests for order validation rejection cases
          - Confirm: order submission reaches Hyperliquid (use testnet)

Step 12:  Points engine
          - xp-events BullMQ processor in worker
          - Referral propagation (3 levels, 10% passthrough)
          - POST /referrals/register
          - leaderboardSnapshot repeatable job
          - GET /leaderboard, GET /me/points
          - Unit tests for XP calculation and referral propagation
          - Confirm: submit a trade → fill → XP event → leaderboard updated

Step 13:  Notifications
          - POST /devices, POST /alerts, DELETE /alerts/:id
          - alertChecker repeatable job
          - send-notification processor (FCM + APNs + SMS fallback)
          - POST /webhooks/onramp
