# 20. FINAL REMINDERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

- When in doubt about the Hyperliquid API shape, check:
  https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs/for-developers/api

- This project will be used as a job application. Treat every file as if
  a senior engineer is doing a thorough code review.

- Prefer explicit over clever. Clear variable names, obvious data flow,
  comments where the "why" is not obvious from the code.

- If you are about to write a TODO or a stub, implement it instead.
  Stubs are fine in Step 1 scaffolding only.

- Every error response must include: { code: string, message: string }
  Dreamcash's mobile app will display these to users.

- The project succeeds when: `git clone` → `docker compose up` → open /docs
  → every route is documented and callable with one command.
  That is the bar. Build to it.
